# Claude Code & Codex: allowlist-only (defense in depth).
# These dirs hold credentials (~/.codex/auth.json), session transcripts,
# sqlite state, caches, telemetry and memories that must never reach this
# PUBLIC repo. Ignore each dir's contents, then re-include ONLY the files
# chezmoi is meant to manage. chezmoi honors .chezmoiignore during
# `chezmoi add`, so this also blocks accidental recursive ingestion of
# secrets/state (e.g. an errant `chezmoi add ~/.codex`).
#
# NB: gitignore/chezmoi cannot re-include a file under an ignored directory,
# so ignore one level at a time (dir/*) and re-include each parent dir we
# need to descend into — NOT dir/** (which ignores the dirs themselves).
.claude/*
!.claude/CLAUDE.md
!.claude/settings.json
!.claude/statusline.sh
!.claude/subagent-statusline.sh
!.claude/themes/
.claude/themes/*
!.claude/themes/tokyo-night.json

.codex/*
!.codex/AGENTS.md
!.codex/config.toml
!.codex/themes/
.codex/themes/*
!.codex/themes/tokyo-night.tmTheme
